Sentencas: Protective Ni-based coatings for stainless steel current collectors of the planar solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) were developed and tested during 21,000 h in contact with lanthanum-strontium manganite cathode material.
Titulo: Composition-gradient protective coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnectors

Sentencas: The compositional and microstructural alterations due to interdiffusion between Ni coating, La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 electrode and commercial Crofer 22 APU steel after long-term testing under the SOFC cathodic conditions, were studied.
Titulo: Composition-gradient protective coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnectors

Sentencas: The results of micro-Raman spectroscopy and electron microscopy analyses showed a dominant role of Mn and Fe diffusion into the protective coating, leading to the formation of NiFe2O4 and MnFe2O4.
Titulo: Composition-gradient protective coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnectors

Sentencas: Although Mn deficiency in the manganite cathode may decrease electrical conductivity, its impact on the overall contact resistance is insignificant.
Titulo: Composition-gradient protective coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnectors

Sentencas: The Ni-based coatings were found to decrease area-specific interfacial resistivity down to 3-4 mOhm x cm(2) for, at least, 21,000 h (>2.5 years) at 1123 K, atmospheric oxygen pressure and current density of 0.5 A/cm(2).
Titulo: Composition-gradient protective coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnectors
